RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEDIA SENSATION stalked in the five path, was put to a ride going into the far turn, under right handed urging from the four path midway around that far turn, tipped back out to the five path into the lane, and drew past an inner rival in the closing stages to win. EMERGENCY RESPONSE prompted the pace in the four path, made a bid early around the far turn and took the lead approaching the quarter, opened up from around the three path into the stretch, and stayed on but was caught late by an outer foe to place. MAKE 'EM TAP bumped with an inner foe at the start, was unhurried in the five path early, under coaxing early around the far turn, floated out to the seven path into the lane, and kept on but had to steady slightly nearing the final sixteenth to finish with show. CHACHARERO bumped with an outer foe at the start, tracked in the two path, received a right handed cue and was under a drive early into the far turn, fanned out to the seven path entering the stretch, and finished evenly. ROYAL FOX HILLS chased along the inside down the backstretch, was ridden around the far turn, but did not factor from around the four path down the lane. SIR GOOSA bumped with an outer foe at the start, set the pace under a hold in the two path early, received a left handed cue when challenged midway around the far turn, but lost the lead and faded in the stretch. KADAR INDY bumped with an inner foe at the start and stumbled slightly just after, rated in the three path early but made no impact. VOICE AN OPINION trailed in the four path early and did not threaten. REDISUR was wellback in the two path and never menaced.
